    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high</p> <p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Separate the <strong>sage</strong> leaves from their stalks, keep a few whole leaves aside for later and chop the remaining finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sage-wrapped-chicken/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and cut the<strong> potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into bite-size pieces</p> <p>Peel the <strong>garlic</strong></p> <p>Add both the <strong>potatoes</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to a pot of <strong>salted</strong> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook over a high heat for 10-20 min or until fork tender&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sage-wrapped-chicken/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rip and tear the <strong>mushrooms</strong> up&nbsp;</p> <p>Tip: ripping the mushrooms creates texture and saves time!</p> <p>Add the ripped <strong>mushrooms</strong> to a baking tray lined with tin foil, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sage-wrapped-chicken/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Place your hand flat on the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Carefully, slice the chicken in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sage-wrapped-chicken/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Place a couple of <strong>sage leaves</strong> over each piece of <strong>chicken</strong>, then wrap each piece of chicken in 2 rashers of <strong>bacon</strong></p> <p>Add the <strong>wrapped chicken</strong> to the tray with the<strong> mushrooms</strong></p> <p>Put the tray directly under the grill and cook for 10-15 min or until the bacon has cooked and crisped and the chicken is cooked through</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sage-wrapped-chicken/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, drain the<strong> potatoes</strong> and leave them in a colander, then return the pot to a medium-low heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p> <p>Add the remaining<strong>&nbsp;chopped sage</strong> and cook for 1 min, then add the potatoes, a big splash of <strong>milk</strong> and <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p> <p>Mash until smooth</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sage-wrapped-chicken/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the<strong> cooked chicken</strong> and <strong>mushrooms</strong> from the grill&nbsp;</p> <p>Transfer the <strong>chicken</strong> to a chopping board to rest a little&nbsp;</p> <p>Sieve the <strong>mushrooms</strong> and<strong> collected juices</strong> into a small pan</p> <p>Add the pan to a low heat and stir in the <strong>clotted cream</strong> until melted, then season with <strong>pepper</strong> - this is your <strong>pan sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sage-wrapped-chicken/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the chicken over the mash with the mushrooms dotted around and the pan sauce spooned over</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
